I"Õ<p style="text-align: justify;">One issue I've found with the built-in WordPress themes (especially the Twenty Sixteen theme) is that when using images in a post they are not aligned correctly on the page.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">After firing up Chrome development tools and checking out the elements on the page it is clear that the main culprit for this is the post comment/date stamp element taking up a big part for the left hand of the page, as shown below:</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-114" src="https://mattselkey.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/2019-01-06-15_55_31-Matthew-S-Key-â€“-IT-_-Scripting-_-Automation-_-Coding-_-Endurance-Sport.png" alt="2019-01-06 15_55_31-Matthew S Key â€“ IT _ Scripting _ Automation _ Coding _ Endurance Sport" width="937" height="286" /></p>

<p>This can easily be fixed by overriding one CSS element.</p>

<p>To do this, logon to your siteâ€™s WordPress, click on â€˜<strong>Appearance</strong>â€™, then â€˜<strong>Edit CSS</strong>â€™.</p>

<p><img class=" size-full wp-image-115 aligncenter" src="https://mattselkey.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/2019-01-06-15_41_21-Dashboard-â€¹-Matthew-S-Key-â€”-WordPress.png" alt="2019-01-06 15_41_21-Dashboard â€¹ Matthew S Key â€” WordPress.png" width="335" height="284" /></p>

<p>Next, click on â€˜<strong>Additional CSS</strong>â€™</p>

<p><img class=" size-full wp-image-116 aligncenter" src="https://mattselkey.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/2019-01-06-15_42_40-Customize_-Matthew-S-Key-â€“-IT-_-Scripting-_-Automation-_-Coding-_-Endurance-Spor.png" alt="2019-01-06 15_42_40-Customize_ Matthew S Key â€“ IT _ Scripting _ Automation _ Coding _ Endurance Spor" width="339" height="209" /></p>

<p>Add the following snippet of CSS into the text box</p>

<p>[cc lang=â€cssâ€ escaped=â€trueâ€  line_numbers=â€trueâ€ nowrap=â€falseâ€]
body:not(.search-results) article:not(.type-page) .entry-content {
float: none;
width: 100%;}
[/cc]</p>

<p>It should appear as shown below:</p>

<p><img class=" size-full wp-image-117 aligncenter" src="https://mattselkey.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/2019-01-06-15_43_12-Customize_-Matthew-S-Key-â€“-IT-_-Scripting-_-Automation-_-Coding-_-Endurance-Spor.png" alt="2019-01-06 15_43_12-Customize_ Matthew S Key â€“ IT _ Scripting _ Automation _ Coding _ Endurance Spor" width="343" height="221" /></p>

<p>Finally click on â€˜<strong>Publish</strong>â€™</p>

<p><img class=" size-full wp-image-118 aligncenter" src="https://mattselkey.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/2019-01-06-15_43_33-Customize_-Matthew-S-Key-â€“-IT-_-Scripting-_-Automation-_-Coding-_-Endurance-Spor.png" alt="2019-01-06 15_43_33-Customize_ Matthew S Key â€“ IT _ Scripting _ Automation _ Coding _ Endurance Spor" width="352" height="159" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Any future posts should appear with the comment/time stamp elements at the bottom of the page and the width of the post should now increase.</p>
